===Noun===
'''springboard'''
#A [[diving]] [[board]] consinting of a [[flexible]], springy, [[cantilevered]] platform.
#In [[gymnastics]], a small platform on springs and usually hinged at one end, used to launch or [[vault]] onto other equipment.
#(figurative) Something that gives [[energy]] or [[impulse]]; something that serves to [[launch]] or [[begin]].
#:''The opportunity served  a '''springboard''' to their success.''

